    <name>
				<text>37.1.10 Resistor boxes</text>
		</name>
    <questiontext format="moodle_auto_format">
				<text><![CDATA[<p class="HELM_exercise">Exercise</p>
<p>A box contains \({@totb@}\) resistors of which \({@vhqb@}\) are deemed to be ‘very high quality’ , \({@hqb@}\) ‘high quality’ and \({@stdb@}\) ‘standard’. In how many ways can a batch of \({@tot@}\) resistors be chosen if it is to contain \({@vhq@}\) ‘very high quality’, \({@hq@}\) ‘high quality’ and \({@std@}\) ‘standard’ resistors? [[input:ans1]] [[validation:ans1]][[feedback:prt1]]</p>]]></text>
		</questiontext>
    <generalfeedback format="moodle_auto_format">
				<text><![CDATA[<h4 class="HELM_solution">Solution</h4>
<p>The order in which the resistors are chosen does not matter so that the number of ways in which the batch of \({@tot@}\) can be chosen is:
\[^{{@vhqb@}}C_{{@vhq@}}\times ^{{@hqb@}}C_{{@hq@}}\times ^{{@stdb@}}C_{@std@}=\dfrac{{@vhqb@}!}{{@vhqd@}!\times {@vhq@}!}\times \dfrac{{@hqb@}!}{{@hqd@}!\times {@hq@}!}\times
\dfrac{{@stdb@}!}{{@stdd@}!\times {@std@}!}= {@ta1@}\]</p>]]></text>
		</generalfeedback>
